  "text": "Durand [CITATION_1] proved that if w is an α-substitutive sequence and h is a non-erasing morphism, then h(w) is α k -substitutive for some k ∈ N. We strengthen this result in two directions. First, we show that k may be taken to be 1; hence h(w) is α k -substitutive for every k ∈ N. Second, we show that Durand's result also holds for non-erasing transductions.",
